To detect [@cucurbit viruses#Virus*] and determine their incidence, [@surveys#Method*] were conducted in 45 fields in 18 villages in Samsun province, Turkey from July to October in 1999 and 2000.
[$Watermelon mosaic virus#Virus*] ([$WMV#Virus*]), [$Zucchini yellow mosaic virus#Plant*] ([$ZYMV#Virus*]), and [$Cucumber mosaic virus#Virus*] ([$CMV#Virus*]) were detected in [$cucurbits#Plant*] after analyzing 165 samples by [$enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay#Method*].
[$WMV#Virus*], [$ZYMV#Virus*], and [$CMV#Virus*] were detected in 53.9, 38.8, and 20.6% of samples tested, respectively.
[$ZYMV#Virus*] and [$WMV#Virus*] infections were detected in all [$cucurbit#Plant*] species, but [$CMV#Virus*] was not detected in any samples of [$watermelon#Plant*] and [$pumpkin#Plant*].
